main event: A civilian observed a white, star-like object in the sky that descended and disappeared over a duration of 5 minutes on May 25, 1960.
interesting points: The object first appeared at 45 degrees above the horizon and descended to 24 degrees before disappearing at 40 degrees., The observer noted the object appeared round and white, resembling a star., It was suggested that the object was not a satellite due to its flight path., The observer indicated the possibility of it being a high-flying aircraft., This sighting came from a civilian engineer located near Bear Lake, 15 miles northwest of Orlando.
sighted object: a white, round object resembling a star
witness description: civilian engineer from South Seminole Ave, Orlando, Florida
